      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "TACOMA, March 25.--Articles OF\nincorporation have been filed here\nfor the Pacific Oregon Railway &\nNavigation CO., which is thought to\nbe backed by Hill. The articles\nsay railroads will be built In Wash\nington. Oregon. Idaho and Califor-\nmia and the company will transact\nsteamship business between Ia\ncoma, San Francisco and other\npoints,\n\n\nThe promoters say one OF the\nfirst steps will be the construction\nof a railroad from the Coos bay\ncounty, In Oregon, 100 miles inland.\ntapping rich agricultural districts.\n\n\nA. II. Law, one of the incorpora-\ntors, was for many years a leading\nofficial of the Northern Pacific."
    }
